message.raw:
minor bug fixes that affect the dContactApprox1 friction model:
(1) the initial nub expansion was too inclusive, the findex variables
    should not have been considered to be unbounded.
(2) in the hit_first_friction_index test we should treat 0*infinity as 0,
    so that mu=infinity can be reliably used with the dContactApprox1
    friction model.

message.raw:
bug fix: the 'degenerate' case where w[i]==0 at the start of the
lcp loop was not handled correctly, resulting in uninitialized
values in L being mixed in with the other computations. this was
fixed by adding a call to lcp.solve1() before lcp.transfer_i_to_C(),
as required by the dLCP API. the solve1() API was changed to allow
quicker computation in this case.
